{
  "texts": [
    "The high error rates across almost all systems indicate that while machine translations can provide a starting point, they often fail to accurately capture the technical nuances of scientific texts.",
    "This finding reinforces the need for expert review and suggests that relying solely on machine translation in this domain may be inadequate.",
    "In conclusion, the analysis highlights the critical role of human oversight, particularly in fields where accuracy and context are paramount.",
    "Machine translations, while beneficial as a starting point, should be complemented with human expertise to ensure fidelity and accuracy, particularly in scientific, psychological, and political texts.",
    "In the next section, we provide a detailed error analysis of the results to understand the root causes of such errors."
  ]
}